obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (67562)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67562&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Criminal Procedure`
  line `(Identification) Act, 2022.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 4th August, 2022, vide notification No. S.O. 3653(E), dated 3rd August, 2022, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (67563)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67563&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) “Magistrate” means,—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a metropolitan area, the Metropolitan Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other area, the Judicial Magistrate of the first class; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to ordering someone to give security for his good behaviour or maintaining`
  line `peace, the Executive Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) “measurements” includes finger-impressions, palm-print impressions, foot-print`
  line `impressions, photographs, iris and retina scan, physical, biological samples and their analysis,`
  line `behavioural attributes including signatures, handwriting or any other examination referred to in`
  line `section 53 or section 53A of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(c) “police officer” means the officer-in-charge of a police station or an officer not below the`
  line `rank of Head Constable;`
  line
  line `(d) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) “prison officer” means an officer of prison not below the rank of Head Warder.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860) and the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall have the same meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in those Codes.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (67564)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Taking of measurement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67564&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Any person, who has been,`
  line
  line `(a) convicted of an offence punishable under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) ordered to give security for his good behaviour or maintaining peace under`
  line `section 117 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) for a proceeding under`
  line `section 107 or section 108 or section 109 or section 110 of the said Code; or`
  line
  line `(c) arrested in connection with an offence punishable under any law for the time being in force`
  line `or detained under any preventive detention law,`
  line
  line `shall, if so required, allow his measurement to be taken by a police officer or a prison officer in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government or the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person arrested for an offence committed under any law for the time being in`
  line `force (except for an offence committed against a woman or a child or for any offence punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a period not less than seven years) may not be obliged to allow taking of his`
  line `biological samples under the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (67572)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Collection, storing, preservation of measurements and storing, sharing, dissemination, destruction and disposal of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67572&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Crime Records Bureau shall, in the interest`
  line `of prevention, detection, investigation and prosecution of any offence under any law for the time being`
  line `in force,`
  line
  line `(a) collect the record of measurements from State Government or Union territory`
  line `Administration or any other law enforcement agencies;`
  line
  line `(b) store, preserve and destroy the record of measurements at national level;`
  line
  line `(c) process such record with relevant crime and criminal records; and`
  line
  line `(d) share and disseminate such records with any law enforcement agency,`
  line
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The record of measurements shall be retained in digital or electronic form for a period of`
  line `seventy-five years from the date of collection of such measurement:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person, who has not been previously convicted of an offence punishable`
  line `under any law with imprisonment for any term, has had his measurements taken according to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, is released without trial or discharged or acquitted by the court, after exhausting`
  line `all legal remedies, all records of measurements so taken shall, unless the court or Magistrate, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing otherwise directs, be destroyed from records.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government and Union territory Administration may notify an appropriate agency to`
  line `collect, preserve and share the measurements in their respective jurisdictions.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (67566)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Magistrate to direct a person to give measurements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67566&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where the Magistrate is`
  line `satisfied that, for the purpose of any investigation or proceeding under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force, it is expedient to direct any`
  line `person to give measurements under this Act, the Magistrate may make an order to that effect and in`
  line `that case, the person to whom the order relates shall allow the measurements to be taken in conformity`
  line `with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (67567)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Resistance to allow taking of measurements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67567&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person who is required to allow the`
  line `measurements to be taken under this Act resists or refuses to allow taking of such measurements, it`
  line `shall be lawful for the police officer or prison officer to take such measurements in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Resistance to or refusal to allow the taking of measurements under this Act shall be deemed to`
  line `be an offence under section 186 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (67568)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Bar of suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67568&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No suit or any other proceeding shall lie against any person for anything done, or`
  line `intended to be done in good faith under this Act or any rule made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (67569)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67569&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or the State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, such rules`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of taking measurements under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of collection, storing, preservation of measurements and sharing,`
  line `dissemination, destruction and disposal of records under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of taking of measurements under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is to be prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to be made.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry`
  line `of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made,`
  line `the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (67570)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67570&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (67571)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196&sectionId=67571&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00043_202211_1659596300196
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Identification of Prisoners Act, 1920 (33 of 1920) is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have done or`
  line `taken including any rule, regulation, or any proceedings taken, any rule made or any direction given or`
  line `any proceedings taken or any penalty or fine imposed under the repealed Act shall, in so far as it is not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard to the effect`
  line `of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
